 The greatest element of a set is its supremum.  Note that the converse is not true; the supremum might not be an element of the set considered.  (Contributed by Jeff Hoffman, 17-Jun-2008.)  Obsolete version of ~ supmax as of 30-Mar-2020.  (New usage is discouraged.) (Proof modification is discouraged.)
